How to Create the Folder Structure
✨ Option 1: Do It Manually (Easy Clicky Way)
Create the main folder:

Right-click > New Folder

Name it: miku_rhythm_game

Inside miku_rhythm_game, create these:

main.py → Right-click > New Text File > Rename it to main.py

beatmap.txt → Same way

Create the assets folder:

Inside miku_rhythm_game, make a folder named assets

Put your files in assets:

Drop in your song.mp3 and miku.png images

⚙️ Option 2: Use Terminal / Command Line
This works on Windows CMD, PowerShell, macOS Terminal, or Linux terminal.

bash
Copy
Edit
mkdir -p miku_rhythm_game/assets
cd miku_rhythm_game
touch main.py beatmap.txt
cd assets
# Add your files here manually (or copy them in)
✅ Now your file tree should look like:

css
Copy
Edit
miku_rhythm_game/
├── main.py
├── beatmap.txt
└── assets/
    ├── song.mp3     ← your Miku song
    └── miku.png     ← a cute Miku image
